AJAX = Asynchronous JavaScript And XML (but can work with Json).

(Ajax is not programming language)

uses ->
a. browser build in XMLHttpRequest object ( to request data from server)
b. js and DOM ( to display or use data)


KEY..
The keystone of AJAX is the XMLHttpRequest object.

Syntax
variable = new XMLHttpRequest();
eg:
var xhttp=new XMLHttpRequest();

To Send Request to Server
------------------------
we use the open() and send() methods of the XMLHttpRequest object:
eg:

GET
---
xhttp.open("GET", "ajax_info.txt", true); //the location can of  File, URL
xhttp.send();

POST  (use to send: more data, more secure)
----
xhttp.open("POST", "ajax_info.txt", true); //the location can of  File, URL
xhttp.send(string); //string as parameter to post operation





